page.title: 20Housing
page.content: In our area there are lots of different kinds of houses of varying ages from the very new to some with quite a history.There are cottages, bungalows,detached and semi detached and terraced houses.Most of the houses are built out of red brick with tile roofs but some are made out of stone.There are a number of farms, including Allandale Farm,Cherry Tree, Gin,Oak and Willey Wood Farms.There are lots of pubs in our area including The White Lion,The Robin Hood,The Yew Tree,The Wagon and Horses,and Underwood boasts a very old pub restaurant called The Hole in the Wall,which attracts people from miles around. There is certainly a great variety of buildings in our area which gives it an interesting appearance.
